accruePrimeInterest(uint16).notice: Accrues prime interest and updates state up to the current block

calculateNTokensToMint(uint16,uint88).notice: Returns the nTokens that will be minted when some amount of asset tokens are deposited

params.amountToDepositExternalPrecision: amount of underlying tokens in native precision

returns._0: the amount of nTokens that will be minted

convertCashBalanceToExternal(uint16,int2.notice: Converts an prime cash balance to an external token denomination

params.convertToUnderlying: true if the value should be converted to underlying
params.currencyId: the currency id of the cash balance
params.primeCashBalance: the signed cash balance that is stored in Notional

returns._0: the cash balance converted to the external token denomination

convertSettledfCash(uint16,uint256,int25.notice: Converts fCash to its settled prime cash value at the specified block time

params.blockTime: block time to convert to settled prime value, must be greater than maturity
params.currencyId: the currency id of the fCash asset
params.maturity: the timestamp when the fCash asset matures

returns.signedPrimeSupplyValue: amount of prime cash to be received or owed to the protocol

convertUnderlyingToPrimeCash(uint16,int2.notice: Converts an underlying balance to prime cash

params.currencyId: the currency id of the cash balance

returns._0: the underlying balance converted to prime cash

getCashAmountGivenfCashAmount(uint16,int.notice: Returns the cash amount that will be traded given an fCash amount, be sure to buffer these amounts slightly because the liquidity curve is sensitive to changes in block time

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.fCashAmount: amount of fCash to trade, negative for borrowing, positive for lending
params.marketIndex: market index of the fCash market

returns._0: net asset cash amount (positive for borrowing, negative for lending) in 8 decimal precision
returns._1: underlying cash amount (positive for borrowing, negative for lending) in 8 decimal precision

getDepositFromfCashLend(uint16,uint256,u.notice: Returns the amount of underlying cash and asset cash required to lend fCash. When specifying a trade, deposit either underlying or asset tokens (not both). Asset tokens tend to be more gas efficient.

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.fCashAmount: amount of fCash (in underlying) that will be received at maturity. Always 8 decimal precision.
params.maturity: the maturity of the fCash to lend

returns.depositAmountPrimeCash: the amount of prime cash tokens the lender must deposit or mint
returns.depositAmountUnderlying: the amount of underlying tokens the lender must deposit
returns.encodedTrade: the encoded bytes32 object to pass to batch trade
returns.marketIndex: the corresponding market index for the lending

getLibInfo().notice: Get a list of deployed library addresses (sorted by library name)

getMarketIndex(uint256,uint256).notice: Returns a market index value for a given maturity

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated

returns.marketIndex: a value between 1 and 7 that represents the marketIndex (tenor) that corresponds to the maturity. Returns 0 if there is no corresponding marketIndex

getPresentfCashValue(uint16,uint256,int2.notice: Returns the present value of the given fCash amount using Notional internal oracle rates

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.riskAdjusted: true if haircuts and buffers should be applied to the oracle rate

returns.presentValue: of fCash in 8 decimal precision and underlying denomination

getPrincipalFromfCashBorrow(uint16,uint2.notice: Returns the amount of underlying cash and asset cash required to borrow fCash. When specifying a trade, choose to receive either underlying or asset tokens (not both). Asset tokens tend to be more gas efficient.

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.fCashBorrow: amount of fCash (in underlying) that will be received at maturity. Always 8 decimal precision.
params.maturity: the maturity of the fCash to lend

returns.borrowAmountPrimeCash: the amount of prime cash tokens the borrower will receive
returns.borrowAmountUnderlying: the amount of underlying tokens the borrower will receive
returns.encodedTrade: the encoded bytes32 object to pass to batch trade
returns.marketIndex: the corresponding market index for the lending

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.marketIndex: market index of the fCash market

returns._0: the fCash amount from the trade, positive when lending, negative when borrowing. Always in 8 decimals.

getfCashBorrowFromPrincipal(uint16,uint2.notice: Returns the amount of fCash that would received if lending deposit amount.

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.borrowedAmountExternal: amount to borrow in the token's native precision.
params.maturity: the maturity of the fCash to lend
params.maxBorrowRate: the maximum borrow rate (slippage protection). If zero then no slippage will be applied
params.useUnderlying: true if specifying the underlying token, false if specifying prime cash

returns.encodedTrade: the encoded bytes32 object to pass to batch trade
returns.fCashDebt: the amount of fCash that the borrower will owe, this will be stored as a negative balance in Notional
returns.marketIndex: the corresponding market index for the lending

getfCashLendFromDeposit(uint16,uint256,u.notice: Returns the amount of fCash that would received if lending deposit amount.

params.blockTime: the block time for when the trade will be calculated
params.depositAmountExternal: amount to deposit in the token's native precision. For aTokens use what is returned by the balanceOf selector (not scaledBalanceOf).
params.maturity: the maturity of the fCash to lend
params.useUnderlying: true if specifying the underlying token, false if specifying prime cash

returns.encodedTrade: the encoded bytes32 object to pass to batch trade
returns.fCashAmount: the amount of fCash that the lender will receive
returns.marketIndex: the corresponding market index for the lending

nTokenGetClaimableIncentives(address,uin.notice: Returns the claimable incentives for all nToken balances

params.account: The address of the account which holds the tokens
params.blockTime: The block time when incentives will be minted

returns._0: Incentives an account is eligible to claim
